<h2 id="strumming-patterns">Strumming Patterns</h2>

<p>Here’s a few ways to strum it, in order of complexity (starting at the easiest version). The “” symbol in the patterns below designates playing the bass note of that chord, for that strum. See my video for reference for all these.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>D   .   C   .   G   .   .   .
1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 +
d   d   d   d   d   d   d   d

D   .   C   .   G   .   .   .
1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 +
d   d   d u d   d   d   d u d

D   .   C   .   G   .   .   .
1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 +
d d d   d d d   d d d   d d d
¯ ¯ &gt;   ¯ ¯ &gt;   ¯ ¯ &gt;   ¯ ¯ &gt;

D   .   C   .   G   .   .   .
1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 +
d d d dud d d dud d d dud d d du
¯ ¯ &gt;   ¯ ¯ &gt;   ¯ ¯ &gt;   ¯ ¯ &gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

